## Instructions
- Continue an existing beat only if the turn meaningfully advances that long goal.
- Mark a beat as `succeeded` or `failed` only when its overarching objective reaches a natural
  conclusion.
- Start at most one new beat per turn, naming it concisely (4-6 words) and summarizing its aim.
- When no beats exist yet, you **must** start one.
- Updates should refine descriptions to reflect new stakes, hazards, or discoveries.

## Output Format
Return strict JSON matching:
{
  "focusBeatId": string | null,              // which beat best fits this turn
  "shouldStartNewBeat": boolean,
  "newBeatTitle": string,
  "newBeatDescription": string,
  "updates": [
    {
      "beatId": string,
      "status": "in_progress" | "succeeded" | "failed" | null,
      "description": string
    }
  ]
}
- `newBeatTitle`/`newBeatDescription` are required when `shouldStartNewBeat` is true.
- `updates` may be empty. Include entries only when something materially changed.
- Keep descriptions under 240 characters. No markdown or commentary outside the JSON.
